# =============================================================================
# Full stack — copy sections into the right files (never commit real secrets).
# =============================================================================
#
# Architecture (market / production mental model):
#
#   [Browser] → Next.js storefront (web/) — UI, SEO, App Router API routes
#                    ↓ Firebase client SDK
#   [Firestore] ← Firebase project — primary database (orders, catalog, users)
#                    ↑ Firebase Admin (server-side)
#   [Razorpay] ← Webhook + REST (keys in web env; webhook hits Next.js /api/...)
#   [Express API] (server/) — optional REST beside Next (CORS + token verify)
#
# Typical cloud split (recommended):
#   • Vercel: import repo with Root Directory = `web/` — set vars from web/.env.example in the Vercel dashboard
#   • Express: Railway/Render/Fly — set vars from server/.env.example
#   • Same Firebase project everywhere.
#
# =============================================================================
# 1) Storefront — web/.env.local   (see web/.env.example for full list)
# =============================================================================
# NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_*=...
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://your-domain.com
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-api-host.example.com
# NEXT_PUBLIC_RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=...
# RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET=...
# RAZORPAY_WEBHOOK_SECRET=...
# FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON={"type":"service_account",...}
#
# =============================================================================
# 2) Express API — server/.env   (see server/.env.example)
# =============================================================================
# PORT=4000
# CORS_ORIGIN=https://your-domain.com
# FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID= / FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL= / FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY=
#
# =============================================================================
# 3) Self-hosted Docker (optional) — copy to .env.deploy and use with compose
# =============================================================================
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:4000
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000
#
# Load Firebase + Razorpay into web container via env_file in docker-compose.prod.yml
